    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pan to a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add a small knob of <strong>butter</strong> with your <strong>cornflour</strong> and cook for 1-2 min or until a sandy paste forms</p><p>Add in your <strong>chicken stock mix</strong> with the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>smoky</strong> <strong>spice mix</strong>, 125ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[190ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[250ml]</span> <strong>cold water </strong>and a pinch of <strong>sugar</strong></p><p>Cook for 3-4 min or until thickened – this is your <strong>spiced gravy</strong></p>",
